Mexican officials found at least 37
bodies, some mutilated, next to a highway near Monterrey,
 Mexico ,  Reforma reported .  The Mexican army and federal police have shut the
Cadereyta-Reynosa highway, the Mexico City-based newspaper
reported, without indentifying the source of information.  Cadereyta is about 40 kilometers east of Monterrey, the
capital of the State of Nuevo Leon and home to some of Mexicoâ€™s
